Geez, Now I am being called a "cheater" by someone because I asked for support from you folks. Unreal!  Some of the contestants in the top 5 are using radio, television, message board forums (that they appear to have joined just for this contest!), bike forums, and a whole host of recruiters of votes!  All I have done is ask for support from a group of you people on OFC that I have considered friends for many years. This truly is a family here and we always go the extra mile for each other. This is clearly within the rules. WFN tells you to use Facebook, Myspace, emails, etc. to promote yourself.  We have to keep voting as much as we can! I'm afraid there is going to be a massive push towards the last couple of days to move people up and I could get bumped from the top 10. My wife and Daughters have put a lot into this for me and I would really like to have at least a chance at being looked at by the panel of judges.  Thanks, Brian

Thanks Dan, Terry, and jr7roo! I have no idea where this coward is coming from, but I doubt he is from ONTARIO, and he certainly does not know me! Having a pond in your backyard does not mean you are financially well off. It means you are 50 years old and have been working (and will continue working for many years to come!)your butt off for 33 years to try and have a place that we can enjoy. The banks do have lots of money...all you have to do is ask for some!  As for transferring fish... they were here when we moved here with the exception of a few Goldfish and some Largemouth fry that I purchased from a fish farm. Otherwise, the fish are reproducing and doing well.  "Charlie" does not seem to mind the Alberta girls using TV, radio, message boards, newspapers and other methods, so my guess is he must be from there?
